summary: The document appears to be a certificate of corporate resolutions related to authorized signers for a corporation. It outlines the powers granted to these signers and confirms that the resolutions are in effect. There are references to the authority of signers and the validity of their signatures.
keyFacts: The document discusses corporate resolutions and authorized signers.
It states that the bank may rely on the instructions of the authorized signers.
It mentions that no one other than the corporation has any interest in the accounts opened in its name.
The document includes provisions for revocation of powers granted to signers not named in the document.
There are references to the need for confirmation by another officer if an authorized signer is also an officer or director.
